data.text:
Bio:

Noomi Rapace (born in Hudiksvall, Sweden on December 28, 1979) is a Swedish actor. She is most widely recognized for her role as Lisbeth Salander in the Swedish film adaptations of The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo, The Girl Who Played with Fire and The Girl Who Kicked the Hornets’ Nest. She’s also appeared in films like Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows, Prometheus and The Drop. She will reportedly play the late Amy Winehouse in an upcoming biopic.

Best Known For:

Noomi is best known for playing Lisbeth Salander in the Swedish film adaptation of The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo.
